The story of the play is as follows: A young man named Pamphilus, son of Laches and Sostrata, used to keep company with one Bacchis. One night as he was going to her house, rather the worse for wine, he met Philumena, the daughter of Phidippus and Myrrhina, on the road, and offered her violence, both of them being ignorant who the other was. ,She could not get any thing from him which could serve as a clue to his recog- nition; but he in the struggle managed to tear from her finger a ring, which he carried to Bacchis and gave to her.
